Package com.github.siroshun09.configapi.api

Interface Configuration

All Known Subinterfaces:
FileConfiguration
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractConfiguration, AbstractFileConfiguration, MappedConfiguration, PropertiesConfiguration, YamlConfiguration
public interface Configuration
An interface that can get a value from a path.

    • getList

      @NotNull <T> @NotNull @Unmodifiable List<T> getList​(@NotNull @NotNull String path, @NotNull @NotNull Serializer<T,​?> serializer)
      Gets the list of the specified path.

      Each element in the list is converted by the Serializer, and those that cannot be converted are removed from the returning list.

      The list stored in this configuration is not changed.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of value
      Parameters:
      path - the path to get the list
      serializer - the serializer to serialize elements
      Returns:
      the serialized list

    • getByteList

      @NotNull @NotNull @Unmodifiable List<Byte> getByteList​(@NotNull @NotNull String path)
      Gets the byte list of the specified path.

      If the byte list could not be obtained, this method returns Collections.emptyList().

      If the list that obtained from getList(String) contains an object that cannot be converted to a number, it will be excluded.

      If the list contains a number that is outside the byte range, it will be converted to a byte using Number.byteValue().

      Parameters:
      path - the path to get the byte list
      Returns:
      the byte list

      byte[] getBytes​(@NotNull @NotNull String path)
